{"name": "graphqlclient", "metadata": {"name": "graphqlclient", "version": "0.2.4", "classifiers": [], "home_page": "https://github.com/prismagraphql/python-graphql-client", "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": "Simple GraphQL client for Python 2.7+", "upload_time": 1531363165}, "documentation": ["# python-graphql-client\nSimple GraphQL client for Python 2.7+\n\n## Install\n\n```sh\npip install graphqlclient\n```\n\n## Usage\n\n\n```py\nfrom graphqlclient import GraphQLClient\n\nclient = GraphQLClient('http://graphql-swapi.parseapp.com/')\n\nresult = client.execute('''\n{\n  allFilms {\n    films {\n      title\n    }\n  }\n}\n''')\n\nprint(result)\n```\n\n### Authorization\n\nAuthorization tokens can be added to the request using the client's `inject_token` method:\n\n```py\nclient.inject_token('very-long-and-secure-token')\n```\n\nwhich defaults to http header name `Authorization`.\nAn alternative http header name for the token can be set by passing in the alternative header name, e.g. for `x-api-key`:\n\n```py\nclient.inject_token('very-long-and-secure-token','x-api-key')\n```\n\n## License\n\n[MIT License](http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)"], "modules": [{"name": "graphqlclient", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "setup", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "setup.long_description", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "graphqlclient.client", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "graphqlclient.client.GraphQLClient", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "graphqlclient.client.GraphQLClient.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "endpoint", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "graphqlclient.client.GraphQLClient.execute", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"na